  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How I make a call in Jio sim?",
  "response": "Making a call with a Jio SIM is straightforward. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide:\n\n1. **Insert the SIM Card**: Ensure that your Jio SIM card is properly inserted into your smartphone. Most modern phones have a SIM card slot where you can insert it.\n\n2. **Network Connection**: Make sure your phone is getting a proper Jio network signal. You should see the Jio network logo in the status bar.\n\n3. **Dial the Number**:\n   - Open your phone\u2019s dialer app.\n   - Enter the phone number you wish to call, including the country code if it's an international number.\n\n4. **Initiate the Call**:\n   - Tap the call button (typically a green phone icon) to start the call.\n\n5. **During the Call**:\n   - You can use the on-screen options to mute the call, put it on speaker, etc.\n\n6. **Ending the Call**:\n   - Tap the end call button (usually a red phone icon) to disconnect the call.\n\n**Additional Notes**:\n\n- Ensure the VoLTE (Voice over LTE) feature is enabled on your device to make voice calls, as Jio primarily operates on the 4G LTE network.\n- If you face issues, ensure your phone is compatible with Jio\u2019s 4G network. Older or non-compatible phones might not support Jio SIM.\n- If you have an active data plan with Jio, you can also use apps like WhatsApp, Skype, or other VoIP services for calling over the internet.\n\nIf you experience persistent issues, consider contacting Jio customer support for further assistance.",
